Place 1 in. water in a small saucepan; add cauliflower. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 5-8 minutes or until crisp-tender. Drain and set aside. In a small skillet, saute celery and onion in butter until tender. Add the cauliflower, bouillon, wine or broth and pepper. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 1 minutes or until heated through. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.